headline: Is It Too Late To Reassess Coca-Cola (KO) After Strong Five Year Share Price Gains
summary: If you are wondering whether Coca-Cola's share price still makes sense after a long run as a household name, this article will walk through what the current market price might be implying about its value. Coca-Cola recently closed at US$78.51, with returns of 6.9% over 7 days, 15.7% over 30 days, 13.6% year to date, 27.6% over 1 year and 81.4% over 5 years, which raises fair questions about how expectations and perceived risk are being priced in. headline: Coca-Cola Exits Frozen Juice Concentrates As Portfolio Story Evolves
summary: Coca-Cola is discontinuing Minute Maid frozen juice concentrates in the U.S. and Canada. The move reflects changing consumer preferences away from frozen juice products. The change affects a long standing category in Coca-Cola's North American portfolio. Coca-Cola, listed as NYSE:KO, is making this product shift while its shares trade at $77.35.
